Package edu.stockton

Class Summary
ATCCommand ATCCommand data object holds the processed command values and contains methods to return them.
Callsign The Callsign data object contains information for a particular airline.
CallsignEngine Identifies aircraft telephony against the callsigns XML library and can look up and convert aircraft information.
Component Represents a component of an ATC command sentence.
Console Console interacts with the Language Processor, as well as the NumberEngine, CallsignEngine, and InstructionEngine using predefined commands.
Instruction Represents a defined and valid ATC instruction, corresponding to an XML node in the instructions.xml data library.
InstructionEngine Recognizes valid ATC commands by checking strings against instructions XML data library.
LanguageProcessor Top level processor responsible for overall ATC command parsing.
Number Represents a number and contains the textual representation, as well as value and weight information for determining numeric value and numeric representation.
NumberEngine General number interpreter.
Param Represents an instruction parameter.
ParsedInstruction Represents an interpreted instruction.
 

Exception Summary
ParseException
